          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The plane is centered in its local coordinate system. For example, a plane of width "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "10.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " extends from "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "-5.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "5.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " along the x-axis. The default width is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "1.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". A width of zero or less creates an empty geometry."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can animate changes to this property’s value. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/animation/animating_scenekit_content"
            },
